pandect
['pandɛkt]
■ noun chiefly historical a complete body of the laws of a country.
⁃ (the Pandects) a 6th-century compendium of the Roman civil law.
Derivatives
pandectistnoun
Origin
C16: from Fr. pandecte, from L. pandecta, from Gk pandektēs 'all-receiver'.
